<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id44a4b8de-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s1021"><num value="1021">§ 1021.</num><heading> Sale of annuities</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In case of the sale of an annuity contract, the adjusted basis shall in no case be less than zero.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id44a4b8df-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/302">68A Stat. 302</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
